    "english_translation": "Narrated by Asim ibn Adi's father: He heard the Messenger of Allah ﷺ when he arrived in Medina asking about a Habashi person called Sayl. He said: Abui passed by him while he was in his house, and said: Where is your family? He said: At Habash Sayl. The Prophet ﷺ said: Take your sandal and garment and go to the Messenger of Allah ﷺ. He said: O Messenger of Allah, this person is from Habash Sayl. The Messenger of Allah ﷺ said to him: Where did you leave your family? He said: At Habash Sayl. The Prophet ﷺ said: Go to your family, for the Hour will not be established until a fire comes out from it like the necks of camels, illuminating from it. He said: I think he said: From Busra.",
